          <p align="left" class="style1"><strong>VISIT US AT BRIGHTWATER   COMMINS - RANDBURG</strong></p>
          <p align="left">On Sunday,&nbsp;6th April 2008, the &lsquo;2 Wheels 4   Justice&rsquo; organisation will hold its annual rally at the Brightwater Commins (old   Randburg Waterfront). In 2007 more than 8000 motorbieks turned up for this   occasion. This year about 15000 bikes are expected, according to the   organisers.</p>
          <p align="left">JB Train Tours will be hosting   again a stall. Come and visit us between 10:00 and 15:00.</p>
          <p align="left" class="style1"><strong>LUISTER na BON VOYAGE op   RSG</strong></p>
          <p align="left">Talle van ons lesers laat weet   dat hulle gereeld vir Johan op <strong>Bon   Voyage</strong> op RSG op &lsquo;n Saterdagoggend hoor praat. Dis lekker om   letterlik landwyd per radio met ons passasiers te kan kommunikeer. O ja,   ons het natuurlik ook luisteraars in Alaska, Australi&euml;, Brittanje, Pole(!) en vele   ander lande.</p>
          <p align="left" class="style1"><strong>NEW TOURS DEPARTING FROM DURBAN</strong><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>
          <p align="left">In the previous issue of our   Newsletter we have mentioned about the new train tours departing from Durban in 2008. The   reaction from our readers was very positive. Details about these tours are   available from us. I.e.: <strong>7   Provinces</strong>, <strong>Namaqualand</strong><strong> Flowers</strong> &amp; <strong>Cape Town Budget   Tour</strong>.</p>
          <p align="left">The August 2008 train tour from   Durban to <strong>Namaqualand Flowers</strong> are fully   booked, but <strong>there is still space</strong> on the 5 &ndash; 12 September 2008 tour.</p>
          <p align="left" class="style1"><strong>NOG NAMAKWALAND   BLOMMETOERE</strong></p>
          <p align="left">Die besprekings op ons <strong>Namakwalandse Blomme trein</strong>toere wat in   Augustus en September 2008 plaasvind, is besig om <strong>in te stroom</strong>. 9 van 10 toere is reeds vol   bespreek (!), maar ons het nou <strong>nog 6 ekstra   treintoere</strong> vanuit Johannesburg &amp;   Pretoria gere&euml;l.   Indien u nog vanjaar wil saamgaan, bespreek <strong>nou</strong>. Die aanduidings is daar dat dit weer   &lsquo;n goeie blommejaar gaan wees.</p>
          <p align="left" class="style1"><strong>RAPPORT het   SAAMGEREIS</strong></p>
          <p align="left">Twee verslaggewers van die   Sondagkoerant, <strong>Rapport</strong>, het saam   op ons KKNK trein van 24 &ndash; 29 Maart 2008 gereis. Besoek gerus hul webwerf en kyk   na die&nbsp; video, foto&rsquo;s en teks op hul webwerf (<A title="http://www.rapport.co.za/" href="http://www.rapport.co.za/" target="_blank">www.rapport.co.za</A>).</p>
          <p align="left" class="style1"><strong>GET YOUR   COPY</strong><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>
          <p align="left">In the latest edition (April   2008) of the <strong>&lsquo;Go&rsquo;</strong> travel magazine,   there is a 32 page supplement about holidaying in <strong>Namibia</strong>.   It is about places to visit plus it has beautiful pictures of our neighbouring   country.</p>
          <p align="left">Kry gerus die April 2008 <strong>&lsquo;Weg&rsquo;</strong> reistydskrif en lees die   heerlike bylae oor Namibi&euml;.<strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>
          <p align="left" class="style1"><strong>2008 RUGBY TRAIN TOURS</strong><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>
          <p align="left">Two train tours have been organised for   2008 to see the Springboks in action. <strong>South Africa</strong> will play <strong>New   Zealand</strong> at <strong>Newlands</strong> in Cape Town on Saturday 16th August   2008. This tour is on the <strong>Premier   Classe</strong> luxury train and flight back to   JHB.</p>
          <p align="left">On Saturday 23rd August 2008   the <strong>Springboks </strong>will play against   the <strong>Wallabies</strong> from   Australia at the <strong>ABSA stadium</strong> in Durban. This tour is on the   Trans Natal Tourism train.</p>
          <p align="left">Bookings for both tours have   opened.</p>
          <p align="left" class="style1"><strong>HUISGENOOT SKOUSPEL &ndash;   2008</strong><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>
          <p align="left">Die 2008 <strong>Huisgenoot Skouspel</strong> by Sun City, waartydens sowat 40 Afrikaanse musiekkunstenaars   optree, vind weer in Oktober 2008 plaas. Besprekings vir die <strong>bus</strong>toere vanaf Pretoria, Centurion, Oos en   Wes Rand, asook vir die <strong>vlieg</strong>pakkette vanaf Kaapstad, <strong>het geopen</strong>. Daar is ook enkele &lsquo;los&rsquo;   kaartjies beskikbaar by twee van die vertonings. Verlede jaar se toerpakkette   was vroeg reeds uitverkoop. Bespreek <strong>NOU</strong>. Al die toerpakkette sluit die   toegangskaartjie tot die Skouspel in.</p>
          <p align="left" class="style1"><STRONG><strong>FEEDBACK &ndash; March   2008</strong></STRONG></p>
          <p align="left">What a &lsquo;lekker&rsquo; busy month:   Boeremusiektrein na KZN, Argus Cycle race in Cape   Town, Two Oceans marathon in Cape   Town, 3 x KKNK toere, St. Dominics Academy   from Newcastle to Stellenbosch for sport and Ho&euml;rskool Centurion se rugbyspan na   die Paarl, as well as the Cape Town Jazz Festival in a joint venture with   Shosholoza Meyl.<strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>
          <p align="left" class="style1"><strong>APRIL 2008 TRAIN   TOURS</strong><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>
          <p align="left"><strong>Cape   Town</strong><strong> -&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong>Our   first Cape Town   holiday tour for 2008. This ever-popular tour will take you to the Mother city   on a 7-day trip: 27 April &ndash; 3 May</p>
          <p align="left"><strong>Motorbikes to Western Cape &amp;   Boland &ndash; </strong>Another Motorbike-on-Train tour to the Western Cape &amp;   Boland: 20 &ndash; 26 April</p>
          <p align="left"><strong>NEW!! -   Motorbikes to Mpumalanga &amp; Lowveld &ndash;</strong>Motorbike-on-Train tour <strong>from</strong> the Western Cape &amp; Boland to the   scenic Lowveld: 15 &ndash; 21 April&nbsp; </p>
          <p align="left"><strong>Durban</strong><strong> Long Weekend &ndash; </strong>Going from Gauteng to the coast.   Enjoy the beach &amp; sea: 24 &ndash; 28 April<strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>
          <p align="left" class="style1"><strong>MAY 2008 TRAIN TOURS</strong><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>
          <p align="left"><strong>Namibia</strong><strong> &ndash; </strong>Enjoy a spectacular 10-day tour to all   the popular tourist destinations in our neighbouring country. 10 &ndash; 19 May &amp;   22 &ndash; 29 May 2008.<strong></strong></p>
          <p align="left"><strong>Durban</strong><strong> Long Weekend &ndash; </strong>Going from Gauteng to the coast.   Enjoy the beach &amp; sea from 1 &ndash; 5 May 2008<strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>
          <p align="left" class="style1"><strong>JUNE 2008 TRAIN   TOURS</strong><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>
          <p align="left"><strong>Comrades Marathon &ndash; </strong>You&rsquo;ve done the training, we   take care of the transport &amp; accommodation: 13 &ndash; 16 June</p>
          <p align="left"><strong>Innibos Kunstefees in Nelspruit &ndash; </strong>Het u geweet dat <strong>Steve Hofmeyer</strong> en <strong>Boney   M</strong> <strong>BEIDE</strong> op Saterdagaand 28   Junie 2008 by Innibos optree EN dat dit op die hoofverhoog is wat deel vorm van   die Feesterrein? Dit beteken geen ekstra betaling vir die &lsquo;show&rsquo; nie! Kom ry   saam met ons op hierdie heerlike jaarlikse toer per luukse bus en oornag twee   nagte in &lsquo;n Bosveld Lodge: 27 &ndash; 29 Junie<strong></strong></p>
          <p align="left"><strong>7 Provinces and 3 Trains &ndash; </strong>Join the tour at just-about-any place in South   Africa, do a circular route and disembark again   at the same station 7 days later: 26 June &ndash; 7 July</p>
          <p align="left">Contact us now for more details about the above tours. The   majority of these tours depart from Gauteng.</p>
          <p align="left" class="style1"><strong>APOLOGY</strong><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>
          <p align="left">Our apologies to everyone who phoned JB   Train Tours by the <strong>end of February</strong> and <strong>beginning of March </strong>2008, but   could not get through to us. Our telephone lines were struck by lightning the   night of te 26th and hence not working for <strong>7</strong> days! We could divert only one of the   incoming lines to a cellphone as long as we were waiting for a Telkom technician   to arrive &amp; do the necessary repairs.</p>
          <p align="left" class="style1"><strong>ACCOMMODATION in the   CAPE</strong></p>
          <p align="left">At JB Train Tours we get various   interesting enquiries and requests about holidaying in South Africa.   Though we are not a travel agent (but an operator), we try to assist as far as   practicle possible. Below is some information about a self-catering 4-bed unit   in the Strand. It is very close to the beach   and other ammenities. <strong>Please contact the   owners directly</strong>.</p>
          <p align="left"><strong><SPAN lang="EN-GB">Houses to let   in safe area &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </SPAN></strong><SPAN lang="EN-GB">Strand, near Cape   Town, Western Cape,   South   Africa.</SPAN><SPAN lang="EN-GB">&nbsp;</SPAN></p>
          <p align="left"><SPAN lang="EN-GB">Two bedroom self catering wooden chalets located in the   lovely False Bay basin and surrounded by the   majestic Hottentots Holland mountain range. Sleeps 4 people and fully equipped.   Bathroom with shower. Very clean and neat. 200 meters from the lovely 3   kilometer long beach of the Strand and 200   meters from a shopping centre. Twenty minutes from Cape Town International Airport. Safe parking &amp; in security   complex. From only R350 per day per house out-of-season and R450 per day during   season.</SPAN></p>
          <p align="left"><SPAN lang="EN-GB">Contact Flip or Jenny Zwiegers:</SPAN></p>
          <p align="left"><SPAN lang="EN-GB"> Email address   :&nbsp; <A title="mailto:annasbb@absamail.co.za" href="mailto:annasbb@absamail.co.za"><SPAN title="mailto:annasbb@absamail.co.za">annasbb@absamail.co.za</SPAN></A></SPAN></p>
          <p align="left"><SPAN lang="EN-GB">Tel: +2782   780 8284&nbsp;&nbsp; +2721 853 2272</SPAN></p>
        </DIV>
        <DIV>
          <p align="left">Regards/Groete</p>
